season to a\ncapacity that will more than double\ntheir present output which, witli the\noperation of the I)KS MOINES rail\nroad will be an important factor in the\nimmediate growth of business in this\nvicinity. George T, Peart will' be tho\nSuperintendent of Construction in tho\nbuilding of these railroads from Caris\nbrook, N. M lo Oklahoma City, Okla\nhoma, nnd the company feels stiro that\nunder his management they will be\nbuilt as speedily as possible commen\nsurate with good work.\nMr. Shepard complimented Raton\nupon its rapid growth and upon the\nbusiness progress apparent.\nHe is pleased With Raton and ex\npressed gratification at its substantial\nbusiness outlook. New Mexican lie\nview. Tho above article appeared in last\nweeks issue of tho Stinta Fo New Mexi\ncan Review, one of the leading papers\nof New Mexico, and will no doubt bo\nof interest and importance to our\nreaders,\nK. I) Shepard, referred to in tlie\nabove article has been at tho head of\nthe Santa Fe, Raton Eastern rail\nroad sinco the beginning of its build\ning. This road extends from Raton\n(or Carlsbrook winch is near Raton) to\nOklahoma City, Oklahoma,\nThe gradn on tho DKS MOINES riuT\nroad, which is tlie west end of tho\nSanta Fe, Raton Eastern, is com.\nploto with tho exception of ono or two\ntulles which is being rapidly built and\nconsiderable grading and contracting\nhas been done on the cast end of the\nroad known as tho Englowood roud.\nMaterial for the road between Ues\nMoines and Raton has been unloaded\nhero at Captilin, .Vigil, Cunningham\nand Carlsbrook, and tho oHIciala say\ntrack will bo laid soon nstho grade can\nbo completed. -Des Moines (N. Mex.)\nihvustjku\nNotice for Publication,\nDepartmttitoftbo Interior, Land OOlc at\nWtodwanl, OUIa. March 5, lft.\nNotice 1 bereurclreu that Edward N. Hal-\nI n-ro. Ueater, Okla. ha Died notice of hi In\ntention to make cominuatlon profln snptort\nof his claim, Tin HE.No3S! A3iiJ5maao Ap.\nrillAMoylMrt, for the K4 NWK A BM\nNE'S'c